{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NsyVrx4G2rLACPqoczKN47","type":"tool_result","content":"A node failed to rejoin the cluster after a restart.\n\nRestore full membership while keeping the cluster healthy.\n\nConstraints:\n- Do not install operators or CRDs.\n- Keep the cluster healthy.\n\nVerification:\n1. Cluster health is yellow/green.\n2. All nodes appear in /_cat/nodes.\n3. app-data remains readable.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n6\n\n[precondition:seed_hosts_index_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_hosts_index_fixture':probe] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A --max-time 5 \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_count\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q \"\\\"count\\\"\"'\n\n[precondition:seed_hosts_index_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_hosts_index_fixture':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -XPUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"settings\\\":{\\\"number_of_shards\\\":1,\\\"number_of_replicas\\\":1}}\" >/dev/null 2>&1; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -XPOST \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_doc\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"msg\\\":\\\"seed\\\"}\" >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\n\n[precondition:seed_hosts_index_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'seed_hosts_index_fixture':verify] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A --max-time 5 \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_count\" >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\n\n===AGENT===\n{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"init\",\"cwd\":\"/mydata/karma/runs/short-rerun/elasticsearch-service-and-network-repair-20260618_115905/stages/stage_02\",\"session_id\":\"ce289871-aa60-457d-913b-8eccb791b18d\",\"tools\":[\"Task\",\"AskUserQuestion\",\"Bash\",\"CronCreate\",\"CronDelete\",\"CronList\",\"DesignSync\",\"Edit\",\"EnterPlanMode\",\"EnterWorktree\",\"ExitPlanMode\",\"ExitWorktree\",\"Monitor\",\"NotebookEdit\",\"PushNotification\",\"Read\",\"RemoteTrigger\",\"ScheduleWakeup\",\"Skill\",\"TaskCreate\",\"TaskGet\",\"TaskList\",\"TaskOutput\",\"TaskStop\",\"TaskUpdate\",\"ToolSearch\",\"WebFetch\",\"WebSearch\",\"Workflow\",\"Write\"],\"mcp_servers\":[],\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"permissionMode\":\"bypassPermissions\",\"slash_commands\":[\"deep-research\",\"design-sync\",\"update-config\",\"verify\",\"debug\",\"code-review\",\"simplify\",\"batch\",\"fewer-permission-prompts\",\"loop\",\"schedule\",\"claude-api\",\"run\",\"run-skill-generator\",\"clear\",\"compact\",\"config\",\"context\",\"heapdump\",\"init\",\"reload-skills\",\"review\",\"security-review\",\"usage-credits\",\"extra-usage\",\"usage\",\"insights\",\"goal\",\"team-onboarding\"],\"apiKeySource\":\"none\",\"claude_code_version\":\"2.1.181\",\"output_style\":\"default\",\"agents\":[\"claude\",\"Explore\",\"general-purpose\",\"Plan\",\"statusline-setup\"],\"skills\":[\"deep-research\",\"design-sync\",\"update-config\",\"verify\",\"debug\",\"code-review\",\"simplify\",\"batch\",\"fewer-permission-prompts\",\"loop\",\"schedule\",\"claude-api\",\"run\",\"run-skill-generator\"],\"plugins\":[],\"analytics_disabled\":false,\"product_feedback_disabled\":false,\"uuid\":\"22db7982-918b-4235-b09c-fb04ee43576c\",\"memory_paths\":{\"auto\":\"